{
  "texts": [
    "Hence the theorem follows from (3-iii) in Theorem 3.1.",
    "The next proposition provides a convenient criterion for a perfect field to be Kummer-faithful.",
    "Proposition 3.3.",
    "A perfect field K is Kummer-faithful if and only if G m (L) div = 0 for any finite extension L of K (i.e., K is torally Kummer-faithful) and A(K) div = 0 for any abelian variety A over K.",
    "The aim of this section is to prove the freeness result for the Mordell-Weil groups over finite extensions of K[σ] modulo torsion."
  ]
}